  "local_port": 52486,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I delete my gmail only from one device and retain the same on other devices?",
  "response": "If you want to delete your Gmail account from just one device but keep it on others, you'll want to remove the account from the device rather than deleting the Gmail account itself. Here's how you can do that for different types of devices:\n\n### Android Device\n1. **Open Settings**: Go to your device's \"Settings\" app.\n2. **Accounts**: Scroll down and select \"Accounts\" or \"Users & accounts.\"\n3. **Select Account**: Find and tap on the Google account you want to remove.\n4. **Remove Account**: Tap \"Remove account.\" You might need to enter your device's pattern, PIN, or password for security reasons.\n\n### iOS Device (iPhone/iPad)\n1. **Open Settings**: Go to the \"Settings\" app.\n2. **Passwords & Accounts**: Scroll and tap on \"Passwords & Accounts\" (or \"Mail\" for older iOS versions).\n3. **Select Account**: Find and select the Gmail account you want to remove.\n4. **Delete Account**: Tap \"Delete Account\" and confirm your choice.\n\n### Windows Computer\n1. **Open Mail App**: Open the Windows Mail app.\n2. **Settings**: Click on the gear icon at the bottom left to open \"Settings.\"\n3. **Manage Accounts**: Click \"Manage accounts.\"\n4. **Select Account**: Click on the Gmail account you want to remove.\n5. **Delete Account**: Select \"Delete account from this device,\" and confirm.\n\n### Mac (Apple Mail)\n1. **Open Mail App**: Open your \"Mail\" app.\n2. **Preferences**: Go to \"Mail\" in the top menu and select \"Preferences.\"\n3. **Accounts Tab**: Click on the \"Accounts\" tab.\n4. **Select Account**: Select your Gmail account from the list.\n5. **Remove Account**: Click the minus button (-) at the bottom to remove the account.\n\nRemember, this process will only remove the Gmail account from the device you're working on. Your email and account data will remain intact on Google's servers and accessible from any other device where the account is logged in.",
